{
  "stem": "1641.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Because they were in fantastic moods.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Quick, quick, quick out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Stand to fives.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Fives, you're lucky if you could get out from the bloody wagon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Jump down from a high platform to the ground, great difficulty.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Anybody that doesn't come out will be shot on the spot.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "So that was additional incentive for me to-- to climb out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "With some difficulty I got out, and tried to stretch my legs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And quick.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "Stand to attention, rows of five.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And then they picked out about 20 young men, not me, luckily, the others who had to go up to the wagons.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "Because they had to-- they had to throw out all the firewood, the dead bodies, which were cluttering up the lovely wagons.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "The wagons had to be used for other purposes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "So they quickly we're throwing out all the bodies, live or dead, doesn't matter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "They're throwing them out on the concrete.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "Half of them are still alive, but unconscious or frozen a bit, or hungry or whatever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "Just throw them out on the concrete.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And just to make sure, the SS men went around and pumped two or three bullets into each lying body.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "The lucky ones were dead already anyhow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "So-- anyhow, quick march.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And so we started our quick march up the hill, a very steep hill.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "I've been back four times since then.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "From the railway station to the Mauthausen camp on the mountain, up on the mountain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "It takes me about one hour to do it now, in a-- in a good condition.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "But then it took about two hours probably, for the people who survived, and who stopped on the way, got their bullet, of course.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
